Job Ref:
We are currently seeking for passionate and dynamic guest focused Front Office professionals who have the ability to deliver exceptional levels of customer service.Responsibilities:To assist the hotel guest in any way possible, according to house policies and to the best of his ability. To supervise the luggage service to ensure a quick and efficient service.To supervise the computer terminal function at the main entrance.To supervise the message delivery ensuring minimum delay. To meet and welcome all arriving guests, ensuring that their needs are satisfied, and that their luggage is swiftly sent to their rooms.To ensure that all check-out room keys are returned to the Front Desk.To ensure an efficient and quick limousine service for the guests.
To be aware of all activities in the hotel and in the city.To maintain an accurate control and record of all luggage left in his charge, and to ensure that all the relevant information is entered in the guest history and log book.To ensure that all function boards are kept up-to-date. To ensure that the hotel's driveway, forecourt and main entrance areas are clean and free of traffic at all times.To ensure that the hotel's flags are raised and lowered as required; are kept clean and in good condition, and replaced as necessary.Qualifications & Experiences Successful candidates should ideally have at least one year experience as a bellman. Good command of English, Arabic would be an advantage.
